TOP Yoruba movie stars and members of the Theater Arts and Motion Picture Producers Association of Nigeria, TAMPAN, have released an awareness video to sensitise their numerous fans on coronavirus. The video, which was released by the Lagos chapter of the association had over eight popular movie stars in it.  The movie stars include Adebayo Salami, Femi Adebayo Salami, Jide Kosoko, Funke Akindele Bello, Faithia Williams, Lanre Hassan, Yinka Quadri, Ayo Adesanya, Yemi Solade, Fausat Balogun, Olaniyi Afonja, and Adekola Tijani. The movie stars dished out information on the effects of coronavirus and why fans need to observe the stay at home order by the government. The movie stars took turns in explaining the need to always wash hands and wear face masks as well as hand gloves to prevent people from contracting the virus.